popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning
Class FNPTask2

java.lang.Object
  popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning.FNPTask2
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable, ComparableTaskObject, java.io.Serializable, TaskObject
public class FNPTask2
extends java.lang.Object
implements ComparableTaskObject

class implements the CKK algorithm (Complete Karmarkar-Karp Algorithm) for 2-way Number Partitioning, due to Richard Korf (1997). This class is almost the same as FNPTask except that it implements the Thread-Local Object-Pool design pattern as a simple array for each thread acting as a stack, without any need for synchronization.

Returns:

run

public java.io.Serializable run()
this is the method that the executor executes (implementing the run() method of the ComparableTaskObject interface that the class implements). It usually creates two more FNPTask2 objects, one corresponding to the decision to keep the two top numbers together, and the other to keep them apart. Then, the two new tasks have to be executed as well, recursively (but may well be submitted to the same executor, one of whose threads is currently executing this task.)

Specified by:

Serializable not used.

newInstance

public static FNPTask2 newInstance(int n,
                                   int sz)
this factory method shall first try to obtain an object from the thread- local object pool of FNPTask2 objects, and if it can't find one, it will then produce an unmanaged one. The _descNumbers array will have length n, and the _sz member will be set to the 2nd arg.
